- title = "How to prepare images for notification"

- content_for :page_title, title

.govuk-grid-row
  .govuk-grid-column-two-thirds
    h1.govuk-heading-xl
      = title

    p
      | You must upload the artwork for the product label.
    p
      | To help National Poison Information Services identify the product,
         you can upload a photo of the product and also its packaging.

    p
      | You can upload up to 10 images. Each file can be up to 30MB, and must be a JPG, PNG or PDF.
    p
      | The image must be in focus and all packaging text legible.
    p
      | The images you need to provide depend on the type of product and how itâ€™s packaged.

    h2.govuk-heading-m
      | Example 1

    p
      | The product has no secondary packaging (for example, a standalone bottle of shampoo).
        You must supply the label artwork and you can supply a clear photo of the bottle.

    h2.govuk-heading-m
      | Example 2

    p
      | The product has secondary packaging (for example, a bottle of shampoo in a box).
    p
      | You must supply the label artwork and a clear photo of the box.
      ' You can also attach the artwork for the bottle label and a photo of the bottle.

    h2.govuk-heading-m
      | Example 3

    p
      | The product contains several components (for example, hair dye).

    p
      | You must supply the artwork and, a photo of the set.
      ' You can also attach the artwork for each bottle label and a photo of each bottle.

    p
      | If the product features instructions or other information on a separate leaflet,
      ' label, tag or card, you must attach this artwork as well
